title: For Sale:   	 WWI GERMAN LUGER PISTOL-ERFURT 1914-MATCHING-RARE
postcontent: Very fine condition WWI German Military Luger pistol in 9mm that was made by Erfurt in 1914. This beautiful gun is all matching numbered including the magazine and both grips. Pistol is serial number #2446 and has a choice original blue finish. The trigger, takedown lever, safety and mag button all have a full original "straw" color. All Imperial markings are crisp and clear and the gun is Unit Marked G.K.122. This unit marking has several possibilities according to reference including "Staff Command" and a "Garde Curassier" regiment. The marking also has the possibility of being police such as Gumbinnen district Kriminalpolizei. Bore is fine and bright with strong rifling. Wood grips have a tight fit with crisp checkering and no cracks or chips and nicely matching numbered on the inside. Mag is also excellant condition with no dents or dings and is matching numbered on the wood base which may be later police added . This great looking and all matching numbered Erfurt 1914 is one of the scarcest and most desireable dates as few were made. Will make a fine addition to a collection. title: For Sale/Trade:  Somaca Belt Sander / Knife Grinder
postcontent:
Somaca 4"X106" glass sander that has been fabricated for knife grinder and or general shop use.  Originally this was a wet sander that had a water tank which the belt ran through and was used to sand glass.  The tank has been removed, the rubber contact wheel has been removed (which I still have) and a flat platen with a tool rest has been installed.  I used this for knife grinding up until recently but I build a 2x72 knife grinder so I have no more use for it.  

The sander uses 4"X106" belts.  I believe the motor is a 1.5 horse but I'm not 100% sure.  The motor has a brake and runs on 120V single phase power.  I also added castors  to the base so it can roll easily around the shop.  It does have tracking adjustment.  I have roughly 20 belts of which about half are brand new and half are used.  They vary in grits but most of them are 50 or 80 grit.  Included is the original contact wheel and arm.

I've made about 10 knives with this sander and it worked really well.  I also used if for sanding wood blocks, aluminum and all sorts of steel.  I'm running out of workspace room in my shop and would like to see what I can get for an offer on it.

Colt’s use of the MaTech flip-up sight is unique among flip-up rear sights in that it has adjustment for both windage and elevation and its slender design allows for maximum peripheral vision when in use giving the shooter the most unobscured view of the target. These are also the reasons that the MaTech flip up rear sight has been the US Military standard for almost a decade.

Designed specifically for the Law Enforcement officer, its lighter platform recognizes the need to minimize weight while not compromising durability as firearms are generally carried for long periods of time and weight becomes a significant factor.

The 16” standard weight barrel is magnetic particle tested after proofing by Colt to ensure every barrel is made of perfect steel with zero flaws. Because of this tight quality control, Colt barrels are durable enough to handle thousands of rounds of highly accurate semi-auto fire yet maintain a lightweight profile. Its 1:7 twist gives it the flexibility to use the widest range of ammunition from 40 grain varmint rounds to 77 grain long range match, while maintaining ballistic stability.

The bolt head is also magnetic particle tested by Colt to ensure all steel surrounding the cartridge is perfect and without flaw. These extra steps of quality are what set Colt rifles apart from other AR-15 type clones.

title: For Sale:  Mossberg 835 12 gauge shotgun for sale.
postcontent:
I have a Mossberg 835 12 gauge for sale. This gun will hold 2 3/4", 3", and 3 1/2" shells. It comes with a 28" accu-choke Vent rib and ported barrel and a Modified choke. Keep in mind this barrel is not meant for rifled slugs of any kind, they can tumble in the barrel due to the porting on the receiver end so if you do want to shoot any type of slug you need a rifled slug barrel or a cylinder bore barrel from a Mossberg 590 6 shot (You will loose the 3 1/2" capability but honestly a 3" slug is already more than enough power)

The furniture is in very good shape with a nice dark stain to it and the bluing is like new. The bore is still really good with not many rounds down the tube. The action is smooth like all Mossbergs should be. The receiver is drilled and tapped for a rail and the mag tube will accept 590 style mag tube extensions. My initial intentions for this gun were to turn it into a potential competition shotgun (3 gun matches) but lost interest in the idea and figured some of the guns need to go, plus I have a wedding coming up later in the year (need funds).

This gun would make a great Turkey, Goose, or duck gun and with a rifled barrel a very capable deer gun. Brand new these retail for $530 in this exact configuration from Mossberg. I am looking for $400. My lose is your gain and I hope it does find a good home soon. With Turkey season starting in a few weeks this would be a great piece to hunt with or just go shoot some clays. Either way you won't be disappointed.
